<font color="#FF0000">THOUGHTS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Sep 25 22:37:39 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
When you are stripped of civilization, and act out the primal drives, you are invincible, single minded of purpose, indistructable, and the leader of the pack. Out of the necessity of survival of the primal ethic of the self, all acts are justifiable. All life other than your own and that of your pack is mere food for the taking, the target of ascendancy, or the victim of a rage.<br><br>
Sounds pretty awful, doesn't it?<br><br>
As I see it, that is what is at the bottom. The removal of civilizing influence by trauma, the raw edge of life in the extreme, or simple survival, is the stage for PTSD. Shay, in &quot;Achilles in Vietnam&quot; describes the berserk state of the Vietnam combatant in some of these terms. It is into that combat mode at the bottom to which I return to neutralize real or imagined fear of a threat.<br><br>
SW, I have been to a few of those places, myself. I truly dissociate on the way down.<br><br>
 
